      "patchset_number": 25,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "I'm a very stupid guy who can't read very well so I decided to test your patch. I removed the postfix: NONE from values and for me the result for cassandra is:\n\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata: \n  annotations:\n    service.alpha.kubernetes.io/tolerate-unready-endpoints: \"true\"\n    \n  name: cassandra\n  namespace: default\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: cassandra\n    helm.sh/chart: cassandra-5.0.0\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: test\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Tiller\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  ports:\n    \n    - port: 7000\n      targetPort: tcp-intra\n      name: tcp-intra\n    - port: 7001\n      targetPort: tls\n      name: tls\n    - port: 7199\n      targetPort: tcp-jmx\n      name: tcp-jmx\n    - port: 9042\n      targetPort: tcp-cql\n      name: tcp-cql\n    - port: 9160\n      targetPort: tcp-thrift\n      name: tcp-thrift\n    - port: 61621\n      targetPort: tcp-agent\n      name: tcp-agent\n  publishNotReadyAddresses: true\n  type: ClusterIP\n  selector:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: cassandra\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: test\n\nSo I don't really know where this default \"headless\" suffix that you mentioned is hidden:(",
      "author": {
